<section id="about">
    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <div class="about-card">
        <div class="about-text">
            <p>Growing up, I didn't just play video games — I wanted to know how they were made. And more importantly, I
                wanted to make my own.</p>
                <p>In 10th grade, while most of my classmates were applying for the usual jobs that come with that degree —
                    trades, electricians, mechanics, office jobs nobody really wanted — my goal was clear: I wanted to
                    become a software developer. Not through university, but through an apprenticeship. My teacher wasn't
                    convinced. He told me my chances weren't good and that I should apply for something more realistic like
                    the others. I applied anyway. I got it.</p>
                    <p>The road after wasn't straight. After my apprenticeship I ended up in IT support, and later as a 2nd
                        Level IT Support for reverse vending machines — not exactly where I imagined myself. On the side I tried
                        building my own thing: a fashion brand, selling 3D printed products. Good experience, wrong passion.</p>
                        <p>What brought me back to coding was an opportunity at work — I was given the chance to automate internal
                            processes. I built a tool, my colleagues used it, asked for more features, and it kept growing. That
                            feeling of building something real that actually helps people — that's what I want to do full time.</p>
                            <p>I want to work on things that challenge me every day — and software development is the only field where
                                I've never stopped learning, even when it wasn't my job.</p>
                                <p>When I'm not coding, I'm at the gym, out running, designing something in 3D, or deep in an anime.
                                    Sometimes all in the same day.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </section>

